title: "Parking space,” means an enclosed or unenclosed, covered or open area or area provided by mechanical means sufficient in size to park vehicles
clause_text: "Parking space,” means an enclosed or unenclosed, covered or open area or area provided by mechanical means sufficient in size to park vehicles. Parking spaces shall be served by a driveway connecting them with a street or alley and permitting ingress or egress of vehicles. "Partition" means an interior non-load bearing barrier, one storey or part storey in height. "Permanent open air space" means air space permanently open;
